                  </persName>
            . I keep the Southampton waggon-office. On the 28th of August, about five o'clock in the afternoon, a truss, weighing above 4 cwt. was brought by Messrs. Thorp's porter, and saw it loaded in the waggon - it started that afternoon about six o'clock. 
               <persName id="t18230910-92-person1018">
